It seemes this Hospitall, and Saint Gregories did not well agree together. For after this, to wit in the yeare 1225. the Proctor and brothers of this Hospitall, sued the Prior and Canons of Saint Gregories, before the Abbat of Feversham, and the Prior and Archdeacon of Rochester (the Popes Deligates, it's like) for the Tithes of Molonde besides Hepyntone, to wit (saith the Leiger Liber. Hosp. Sti 
                  Lawrentii.
               ) of 80 Acres of Land of the Earle of Glocesters Fee; but with what successe I doe not finde.
